	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=16453&mid=107063844213324>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=16453&mid=107063844213324>RE: SOE at it again</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=16453&mid=107063844213324#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Dec 5th 10:34 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=86707><span id=Scholar>Yalar</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>64 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.87]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>*Quite a rant this one. Ended up being a pro-wizard argument so this maybe isn't the right place for it, but read and enjoy or just stop reading here*<br><br>I don't have Mana Burn and I complain about the nerfing because that is why I have never bothered with it. Frankly it is too situational these days to waste AA on in my opinion, until maybe you have bought everything else you might want. Al'Kabor... Yes well, useless spell line as is, but in my opinion it can't be fixed to something useful without overpowering it. LinusMundane is correct about the AEs though, that's where you have your farming tool and AE group fun if you like that. Read me right now, I love my wizard and it's quite frankly the only class I really really ever enjoyed playing.<br><br>What people fail to see when they whine about being wizards is the utility wizards can bring to a group. We don't necessarily do the most damage in very long fights, if you bring Mage pets and other factors into the calculation. We do however pull our weight, outdamage most classes in most situations, and have the power to save our friends asses in more than just one way when the going gets tough. <br><br>Telekin, lovely spell, all our stuns are but with PoP this one shines the most. Especially if teamed up with Concussion. Some wizards argue Concussion isn't worth it. I think they are so very wrong, but everyone plays the way they see fit. To me it is invaluable in groups and even has some use on certain raids mobs. It's without a doubt the spell I have most casts on during my career. Draught of Thunder is a killer on those gating/healing mobs. Even stun resistant mobs have a hard time channeling through the combined effort of 2 or 3 wizards using just this low mana fast cast spell while the tanks pound them down. Spellshield and the new Protection of Calrena can really help out in a close fight against those procing mobs. Saved my tank plenty of times against BoT mobs. Allegiant Familiar, gotta love the little bugger, brings us up to the very top of the class as far as mana regen goes due to the fact that we can have it alongside all other classes regen buffs, and then there's the resists too. And while we're on the subject, let's not forget Harvest and Harvest of Druzzil, they really do help out a lot. Some other classes have similiar things, but hey, who am I to point fingers, I'm happy with the extras I got. <br><br>Now let's look at the crits. We are the masters of this, don't you doubt it. Mages, druids etc need their crits to be useful in comparison. If they didn't get the AA to crit they would fall too far behind a maxed AA wizard. No matter how many AAs you have on crits you go through down periods now and then and so does anyone, but on a good mob you easily press out a 8-10/1 damage/mana ratio. <br><br>Oh yeah and we have our evacs and ports too. Not always fun being a port bitch, but there should be at least 1 wizard on any given raid to help with transportation to, and more critically, out of dungeons. Druids can somewhat fill this role, but not nearly with the same versatility. Our little innate resist check modifier shouldn't be forgotten. Maybe doesn't do much when you look on a single nuke, but punch it out over a few hours raiding and I'm pretty sure we dealt out some extra damage where anyone else would have been resisted. Which brings us to raids... Lures will kill your mob when mages and druids are transformed to dead weight in the back of the line as far as nuking goes (Not bashing mages and druids here, in such a case these very versatile classes have other duties to perform to help out and they sure do their part as well)<br><br>My point is simply this: Wizards are not just some extra DPS in the back. We are extra DPS, not always with the extra agro people think. A means to get there and out again without any trouble. Corpse draggers (with both IVU and reg. invis) and life savers. The remedy against proc deaths and the finger in the gating mobs face. <br><br>This is all in the perspective of a 65 wizard with around 130 AAs. I have no &quot;uber&quot; gear and things can always get better with more stuff and more AA. During my career there have been up and down periods for my class. Luckily for me I had friends playing with me anyway when something else would have been more useful. And then there's always the quading. Very useful and efficient, but for gods sake don't forget to learn how to play in a group. So in the end I've had my ups and downs, I have been to places where I was all but useless but I have also been the 1 guy keeping a group alive and in the fight. Now... There's always things I want to see fixed and improved, but in the big picture I couldn't be more pleased.<br><br>Oh yeah and to keep this post on something that actually makes it valid for the forum. The book should go to any int or wis caster who would be upgraded by the Phylactery quest. The uses this thing may have of it's own is so minor in comparison if you ask me. How you chose to award loot in your guild/raid decides how it's done. <br><br>T-Bird<br>Proud Einherjar of Zebuxoruk<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Dec&nbsp;&nbsp;5 10:44:53 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
